# Diabetes Prediction ML

## Overview
This project explores diabetes prediction from clinical health indicators using Python and machine learning techniques. The workflow includes exploratory data analysis, preprocessing, class balancing, feature selection, model comparison and hyperparameter tuning.

## Dataset
The project uses a dataset of more than 250,000 records containing clinical and health-related indicators associated with diabetes prediction.

## Technologies
- Python
- Pandas
- NumPy
- Matplotlib
- Scikit-learn
- XGBoost
- Google Colab

## Project Workflow
- Exploratory data analysis
- Data preprocessing
- Class imbalance analysis
- Feature selection
- Model training and comparison
- Hyperparameter tuning
- Performance evaluation

## Models Explored
- Dummy Classifier
- Logistic Regression
- Decision Tree
- Random Forest
- KNN
- Gradient Boosting
- XGBoost
- Naive Bayes

## Key Methods
- SMOTE
- Undersampling
- SelectKBest
- RFE

## Results
This project compares multiple machine learning approaches for diabetes prediction and evaluates their performance using appropriate classification metrics.

